# Astro Starter - Layout and Naming Conventions

This project uses a Relume-aligned naming convention for seamless Figma-to-code workflow with the Relume Figma Kit.

## Core Principle: Numbers vs Props

```
Numbers = Different STRUCTURE (different HTML/layout)
Props   = Different CONFIGURATION (same structure, different styling)
```

### When to Create a NEW Numbered Variant
- Different HTML structure
- Different visual layout (centered vs split, single vs two-column)
- Different content arrangement

### When to Use PROPS on Existing Component
- Padding/spacing variations (`size`, `paddingTop`, `paddingBottom`)
- Background color changes (`background`)
- Alignment options (`align`, `centered`)
- Container width (`containerWidth`)

## Naming Convention by Component Level

| Level | Convention | Example |
|-------|------------|---------|
| **Atoms** | Base name + variant props | `Button variant="primary"` |
| **Molecules** | `{Type}{Number}` | `Card1`, `Card2`, `Card3` |
| **Organisms** | `{Category}{Number}` | `Header1`, `Hero1`, `CTA1`, `Footer1` |

## CSS Class Naming Pattern

Use `{category}{number}_{element}` with underscore separator:

```css
/* Correct */
.hero1_heading { }
.hero1_content { }
.hero1_actions { }
.cta2_grid { }
.cta2_image-wrapper { }
.card1_body { }

/* Incorrect - avoid these patterns */
.hero__heading { }      /* BEM double underscore */
.hero-heading { }       /* No component number */
.heroHeading { }        /* camelCase */
```

## Standard Props for Section Organisms

All section organisms should accept these configuration props:

```typescript
interface SectionProps {
  // Padding control
  size?: 'sm' | 'md' | 'lg';
  paddingTop?: 'none' | 'sm' | 'md' | 'lg';
  paddingBottom?: 'none' | 'sm' | 'md' | 'lg';
  
  // Background
  background?: 'default' | 'muted' | 'primary' | 'dark';
  
  // Container
  contained?: boolean;
  containerWidth?: 'small' | 'medium' | 'large' | 'full';
}
```

## Current Component Inventory

### Atoms (Base names, no numbers)
- `Button` - with `variant` prop for primary/secondary/ghost
- `Badge` - with `variant` prop for colors
- `Input` - with `size` prop
- `Avatar` - with `size` and `shape` props
