## File Structure

```
src/components/
├── atoms/           # Base names, variants via props
├── molecules/       # Numbered variants for structural differences
├── organisms/       # Always numbered (Relume-aligned)
└── templates/       # Page layouts (BaseLayout, etc.)
```

## Creating New Components

### Adding a New Organism Variant

1. Identify the category (Hero, CTA, Feature, Layout, etc.)
2. Check existing variants to determine the next number
3. Create file: `{Category}{NextNumber}.astro`
4. Use CSS class prefix: `.{category}{number}_`
5. Include standard section props (size, paddingTop, paddingBottom, background)
6. Export from `organisms/index.ts`

### Adding a New Molecule Variant

1. Identify the type (Card, etc.)
2. Only create a numbered variant if structure differs significantly
3. Create file: `{Type}{NextNumber}.astro`
4. Use CSS class prefix: `.{type}{number}_`
5. Export from `molecules/index.ts`

## Import Patterns

```astro
// Preferred: Direct imports
import Hero1 from '../components/organisms/Hero1.astro';
import Card1 from '../components/molecules/Card1.astro';
import Button from '../components/atoms/Button.astro';

// Also valid: Barrel imports
import { Hero1, CTA1, Feature1 } from '@organisms';
import { Card1, Card2 } from '@molecules';
```

## Mapping Relume Components

When importing from Relume Figma Kit:
- `Layout 47` → Create `Layout47.astro` if significantly different, or map to existing `Layout1` if similar
- `CTA 5` → Create `CTA5.astro` following the established pattern
- Use the same number as Relume when possible for easy reference
